ZH: 他们经常吵嘴，但是他们还是很喜欢对方。
EN: They argue a lot, but they still love each other.

ZH: 我们昨天吵嘴了，现在我们都有点生气。
EN: We had an argument yesterday, and now we are both a little upset.

ZH: 她们说了很多难听的话，只是为了吵嘴。
EN: They said a lot of mean things just to argue.

ZH: 每次他们吵嘴，都会吵得很激烈。
EN: Every time they argue, it gets very intense.

ZH: 他们之间的吵嘴让周围的人很尴尬。
EN: The argument between them makes everyone around feel awkward.

ZH: 不要总是吵嘴，我们可以好好谈一谈。
EN: Don't always argue, we can talk things out calmly.

ZH: 吵嘴并不是解决问题的最好方式。
EN: Arguing isn't the best way to solve problems.

ZH: 我们之间不应该老是吵嘴，以后要好好沟通。
EN: We shouldn't always argue, we should communicate better in the future.

ZH: 吵嘴只会让事情变得更糟糕。
EN: Arguing will only make things worse.

ZH: 他们已经吵了一个晚上嘴了，还没有停下来。
EN: They have been arguing all night and haven't stopped yet.

ZH: 我们家人吵嘴时总是大声吵，让邻居都听得到。
EN: Our family always argues loudly, so the neighbors can hear.

ZH: 他们吵嘴时总是忘记了彼此的感受。
EN: They always forget each other's feelings when they argue.

ZH: ​他们之间的吵嘴让气氛变得很紧张。
EN: The argument between them made the atmosphere very tense.

ZH: 最近他们之间吵嘴的次数比以往更多。
EN: Recently, they have been arguing more than usual.

ZH: 吵嘴时要说出真正的想法，不要隐瞒。
EN: When arguing, speak your true thoughts, don't hide them.

ZH: 他们吵嘴的原因通常是因为沟通不畅。
EN: The reason they argue is usually due to poor communication.

ZH: 他们吵嘴吵得非常厉害，最后都生气地走开了。
EN: They argued so fiercely that they both stomped off angrily.

ZH: 他们吵嘴的声音让孩子们很害怕。
EN: The sound of their argument scared the children.

ZH: 吵嘴时要注意说话的方式和语气。
EN: Pay attention to your tone and way of speaking when arguing.

ZH: ​他们吵嘴不是为了伤害对方，只是为了表达自己的观点。
EN: They argue not to hurt each other, just to express their opinions.
